<!--
  IL2CPP engine-code stripping (`stripEngineCode`, on by default for Android) drops engine
  classes the managed code never *names*. Nothing in this project names CapsuleCollider — but
  GameObject.CreatePrimitive attaches one to every Cylinder it builds, and the cup, mug, both
  pencils and the five keep markers are cylinders.

  Without this the device log fills with "Can't add component because class 'CapsuleCollider'
  doesn't exist!", and earlier it did worse: dereferencing the collider that was never added
  threw inside KitchenBuilder.Build and left the entire 3D scene unbuilt while the flat UI still
  drew (see Docs/HANDOFF.md section 2).

  We do not actually want the collider — every cylinder deletes it immediately — but
  CreatePrimitive insists on adding one, so the class has to survive into the build.
-->
<linker>
  <assembly fullname="UnityEngine.PhysicsModule">
    <type fullname="UnityEngine.CapsuleCollider" preserve="all" />
  </assembly>
</linker>
